_refine_special_details
;

The crystal under investigation was found to be non-merohedrally 
twinned. The orientation matrices for the two components were 
identified using the program Cell_Now, with the two components 
being related by a 180 degree rotation around the reciprocal 
a- or c-axis (twin transformation matrix -1 0 -1.421, 0 -1 0, 
0 0 1).

The two components were attempted to be integrated using Saint from 
the Bruker AXS suite of programs. Integration proofed problematic 
due to excessive multiple overlap of reflections, resulting in an 
excessive numbers of rejected reflections and poor data quality. 
Attempts were made to adjust integration parameters to avoid excessive
rejections (through adjustments to integration queue size, blending of
profiles, integration box slicing and twin overlap parameters), which
led to less but still substantial numbers of rejected reflections.
With no complete data or good quality set obtainable through 
simultaneous integration of both twin domains, the data were instead 
handled as if not twinned, with only the major domain integrated, and 
converted into an hklf 5 type format hkl file after integration using 
the "Make HKLF5 File" routine as implemented in WinGX. The twin law 
matrix was used as obtained from SAINT, see above. The Overlap R1 and 
R2 values used were 0.55, i.e. reflections with a discriminator 
function less or equal to overlap radius of 0.55 were counted 
overlapped, all others as single. The discriminator function used was 
the "delta function on index non-integrality". No reflections were 
omitted.

The structure was solved using direct methods with the hklf 4 type
file and was refined using the hklf 5 type file, resulting in a BASF
value of 0.310(6).

No Rint value is obtainable for the hklf 5 type file using the WinGX
routine. The value from the data before application of detwinning is 
given instead. 

The lead ion was refined as 1:1 disordered over two symmetry equivalent 
positions around a two fold axis. The iodine atoms in equatorial 
positions around the lead ion are 1:1 disordered around inversion 
centers. This disorder induces 1:1 disoder of the ammonium ions hydrogen 
bonded to the iodine atoms, and the disorder extends into the bridging 
ethylene unit of the ligand. The two disordered NH3+-CH2-CH2- moieties 
were restrained to have similar geometries. Uij components of ADPs for 
disordered C and N atoms closer to each other than 2.0 Angstrom were 
restrained to be similar. 
;
